					Full Description



Aly Energy Services, Inc., incorporated on August 3, 1992, provides oilfield services, including surface equipment rental, solids control services and directional drilling services, to exploration and production companies. The Company provides a range of oilfield services to owners and operators of oil and gas wells. The Company offers services under various categories, including surface rental equipment, solids control systems, and directional drilling and measurement-while-drilling (MWD) services. The Company's equipment and services are primarily designed for and used in land-based horizontal drilling. Its equipment includes centrifuges and auxiliary solids control equipment, mud circulating tanks (MCTs) and auxiliary surface rental equipment, portable mud mixing plants, containment systems, and MWD kits.The Company owns over 80 centrifuges. It provides three different sizes of centrifuges, including SS800, SS1000 and SS2000. It has approximately 110 vertical 400-barrel MCTs and over 140 500-barrel MCTs. MCTs are rented with auxiliary equipment, such as diesel or electric mud pumps, hoses and wooden mats. The Company owns approximately 10 mud mixing plants ranging in size from 60-barrel capacity to 400-barrel capacity. Its containment systems consist of berms and plastic linings constructed to ensure that all products and chemicals present on the well site, particularly those which might be environmentally undesirable if spilled, are contained. The Company's MWD kits provide data while remaining stable over a temperature range.The Company provides solids control services. It rents a package of solids control equipment to the customers which includes approximately two centrifuges, shakers, vertical dryers, waste removal units and/or various tanks. It offers full directional drilling packages and MWD only services, which include both equipment, such as downhole motors and MWD kits, and personnel, such as experienced directional drillers and MWD operators, at one package day rate. The Company offers hauling of its rental equipment to the well site and rig-up/rig-down of such equipment. The Company fabricates certain equipment in its rental fleet, including approximately 400-barrel MCTs, mud mixing plants and MWD kits. Fabrication takes place in its facilities in Giddings, Texas and in Houston, Texas. The Company services the Permian Basin (in Texas and New Mexico), Eagle Ford Shale, Utica Shale, Marcellus Shale, Woodford Shale, Granite Wash, Mississippian Lime and Tuscaloosa Marine Shale.

» Full Overview of ALYE.PK







